page.title: 07INTERVIEW ..cont.
page.content:
(cont.)
There are not many houses,but the ones present are relatively big and quite old.No drastic changes have occured,although a large building and two new stables have been erected.
Mrs Nuttal says that most people in the low-populated belong to the Church of England.She also states that she likes the area very much because it is peaceful (only a few cars travel down the windy lanes.) There is no real history in this area although Mrs.Nuttal says that there is evidence of an old track which runs through the fields.
